# core: shared business logic only

The `core/` module is shared library code for reusable cloud business logic (for example `core/cost` and `core/account`) from caller-provided credentials. It must not know about local machine configuration.

## Forbidden in core/

- `os/exec`, shelling out, or references to external CLIs
- `~/.aws/credentials`, `~/.aws/config`, finops config files, or profile names
- Authentication methods (SAML, profile), login flows, or credential file I/O
- Naming specific binaries in comments, errors, or constants

## Where local configuration belongs

- **`cli/internal/aws`** — credentials files, STS validation, SAML/profile login, assume-role, profile loading
- **`cli/internal/awsauth`** — auth-method selection and ensure orchestration
- **`cli/internal/configstore`** — finops config file

## Where reusable cloud operations belong

- **`core/cost`** — cloud cost query and aggregation logic (no local config reads)
- **`core/account`** — reusable account metadata operations (tags, account names, org-based account kind detection) using caller-supplied `aws.Config`
- Keep these operations callable from CLI and future API layers without duplication

## Patterns

```go
// ✅ GOOD — caller passes an authenticated aws.Config
type AccountTarget struct {
    AccountID  string
    AWSConfig  aws.Config
}

// ✅ GOOD — optional hook for org account names (uses passed Config, not files)
type AWSFetchOptions struct {
    ListAccountNames func(context.Context, aws.Config) (map[string]string, error)
}

// ❌ BAD — reading profiles or credentials paths in core
path, _ := DefaultCredentialsPath()
```

`core/*` packages call cloud APIs using caller-supplied `aws.Config` only.
